#python # use "include two_link_control" to get external two_link_control.py program
def sysCall_thread(): sim.setThreadAutomaticSwitch(True) print( "From threaded Python child script, threadMain")
joint1 = sim.getObject('./joint1') joint2 = sim.getObject('./joint2') link1 = sim.getObject('./link1') link2 = sim.getObject('./link2')
velocity1 = 0 velocity2 = 0 hammer_back1 = 0 hammer_back2 = 0 torque1 = 0 torque2 = 0 orientation1 = sim.getJointPosition(joint1,sim.handle_world) orientation2 = sim.getJointPosition(joint2,sim.handle_world)
while sim.getThreadExistRequest() == False: message, auxiliaryData, auxiliaryData2 = sim.getSimulatorMessage() if (message == sim.message_keypress): if (auxiliaryData[0] == ord("w")): print("w is pressed") velocity1 = 100 torque1 = 200 hammer_back1 = 0 if (auxiliaryData[0] == ord("s")): print("s is pressed") hammer_back1 = 1 torque1 =-200 velocity1 = -100 if (auxiliaryData[0] == ord("a")): print("a is pressed") velocity2 = 100 torque2 = 200 hammer_back2 = 0 if (auxiliaryData[0] == ord("d")): print("d is pressed") hammer_back2 = 1 torque2 =-200 velocity2 = -100 if hammer_back1 == 1: sim.setJointPosition(joint1, -1, orientation1) if hammer_back2 == 1: sim.setJointPosition(joint2, -1, orientation2) sim.setJointTargetPosition(joint1, velocity1) sim.setJointTargetPosition(joint2, velocity2)
